# Playoff Teams & Runs Created: A Love Story .. I mean Case Study

It is no surprise the name of the game of baseball is to outscore the opponent. Runs Created was a sabermetric statistic created by the late-great Bill James. According to MLB.com, it estimates a player's offensive contribution in terms of total runs. It combines a player's ability to get on base with his ability to hit for extra bases. Then it divides those two by the player's total opportunities.

